%% Authentication Flow - Complete Better Auth Authentication Sequence
%% This diagram shows three authentication scenarios:
%% A. Sign Up Flow - New user registration
%% B. Sign In Flow - Existing user login
%% C. Protected Route - Authenticated request

sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Web as Frontend (Web/Admin)
    participant AuthUI as Better Auth SDK
    participant AuthAPI as Better Auth Backend
    participant API as Hospeda API
    participant DB as Database

    %% ========================================
    %% SCENARIO A: SIGN UP FLOW
    %% ========================================
    Note over User,DB: 🆕 Scenario A: Sign Up Flow

    User->>Web: Navigate to /auth/signup
    activate Web

    Web->>AuthUI: Render <SignUp />
    activate AuthUI

    AuthUI-->>User: Display signup form
    deactivate AuthUI

    User->>AuthUI: Fill form (email, password, name)
    activate AuthUI

    AuthUI->>AuthUI: Validate input (client-side)

    AuthUI->>AuthAPI: POST /v1/sign_ups
    activate AuthAPI

    AuthAPI->>AuthAPI: Validate credentials
    AuthAPI->>AuthAPI: Hash password
    AuthAPI->>AuthAPI: Create Better Auth account
    AuthAPI->>AuthAPI: Generate session token

    AuthAPI-->>AuthUI: Session created (authUserId, JWT)
    deactivate AuthAPI

    AuthUI->>AuthUI: Store session in cookie
    AuthUI->>Web: Trigger redirect to /auth/signup-callback
    deactivate AuthUI

    Web->>Web: Extract authUserId from session
    Web->>API: POST /api/v1/public/auth/signup<br/>{authUserId, email, firstName, lastName}
    activate API

    API->>API: Validate request body (Zod)
    API->>DB: INSERT INTO users (auth_provider_user_id, email, first_name, last_name)
    activate DB

    alt User Created Successfully
        DB-->>API: User record created
        deactivate DB

        API-->>Web: { success: true, user: {...} }
        deactivate API

        Web->>Web: Store user data in state
        Web->>Web: Redirect to /dashboard
        Web-->>User: Show dashboard (authenticated)
        deactivate Web

    else Database Error
        DB-->>API: Error (constraint violation, etc.)
        deactivate DB

        API->>API: Log error
        API-->>Web: { success: false, error: 'USER_CREATION_FAILED' }
        deactivate API

        Web->>AuthAPI: Sign out user (cleanup)
        Web-->>User: Show error message
        deactivate Web
    end

    %% ========================================
    %% SCENARIO B: SIGN IN FLOW
    %% ========================================
    Note over User,DB: 🔐 Scenario B: Sign In Flow

    User->>Web: Navigate to /auth/signin
    activate Web

    Web->>AuthUI: Render <SignIn />
    activate AuthUI

    AuthUI-->>User: Display signin form
    deactivate AuthUI

    User->>AuthUI: Enter credentials (email, password)
    activate AuthUI

    AuthUI->>AuthAPI: POST /v1/sessions
    activate AuthAPI

    AuthAPI->>AuthAPI: Validate credentials
    AuthAPI->>AuthAPI: Verify password hash

    alt Valid Credentials
        AuthAPI->>AuthAPI: Generate session token (JWT)
        AuthAPI-->>AuthUI: Session created (JWT)
        deactivate AuthAPI

        AuthUI->>AuthUI: Store session in cookie
        AuthUI->>Web: Trigger redirect to /auth/signin-callback
        deactivate AuthUI

        Web->>Web: Extract authUserId from session
        Web->>API: POST /api/v1/public/auth/signin<br/>{authUserId}
        activate API

        API->>DB: SELECT * FROM users WHERE auth_provider_user_id = ?
        activate DB

        alt User Exists
            DB-->>API: User record found
            deactivate DB

            API->>API: Update last_login timestamp
            API-->>Web: { success: true, user: {...} }
            deactivate API

            Web->>Web: Store user data in state
            Web->>Web: Redirect to /dashboard
            Web-->>User: Show dashboard (authenticated)
            deactivate Web

        else User Not Found
            DB-->>API: No user found
            deactivate DB

            API->>DB: INSERT INTO users (auth_provider_user_id, ...)
            activate DB
            DB-->>API: User created
            deactivate DB

            API-->>Web: { success: true, user: {...} }
            deactivate API

            Web->>Web: Redirect to /onboarding
            Web-->>User: Show onboarding flow
            deactivate Web
        end

    else Invalid Credentials
        AuthAPI-->>AuthUI: Authentication failed
        deactivate AuthAPI

        AuthUI-->>User: Show error message
        deactivate AuthUI
        deactivate Web
    end

    %% ========================================
    %% SCENARIO C: PROTECTED ROUTE
    %% ========================================
    Note over User,DB: 🛡️ Scenario C: Protected Route Access

    User->>Web: Navigate to /accommodations/create
    activate Web

    Web->>AuthUI: useAuth() - Check session
    activate AuthUI

    alt Session Exists
        AuthUI->>AuthUI: Validate session token
        AuthUI-->>Web: { isSignedIn: true, userId: 'auth_user_123' }
        deactivate AuthUI

        Web->>Web: Render protected page
        Web-->>User: Display accommodation creation form
        deactivate Web

        User->>Web: Submit form (create accommodation)
        activate Web

        Web->>AuthUI: getToken() - Get JWT
        activate AuthUI
        AuthUI-->>Web: JWT token
        deactivate AuthUI

        Web->>API: POST /api/v1/accommodations<br/>Authorization: Bearer {JWT}
        activate API

        API->>API: Extract Authorization header
        API->>AuthAPI: Verify JWT signature
        activate AuthAPI

        alt Valid JWT
            AuthAPI->>AuthAPI: Validate token signature
            AuthAPI->>AuthAPI: Check expiration
            AuthAPI-->>API: Token valid { userId: 'auth_user_123' }
            deactivate AuthAPI

            API->>DB: SELECT * FROM users WHERE auth_provider_user_id = 'auth_user_123'
            activate DB
            DB-->>API: User record (id, role, permissions)
            deactivate DB

            API->>API: Create actor context<br/>{ id: 'uuid', role: 'OWNER', ... }
            API->>API: Check permissions (createAccommodation)

            alt Has Permission
                API->>API: Create accommodation (service layer)
                API->>DB: INSERT INTO accommodations (...)
                activate DB
                DB-->>API: Accommodation created
                deactivate DB

                API-->>Web: { success: true, data: {...} }
                deactivate API

                Web-->>User: Show success message + redirect
                deactivate Web

            else No Permission
                API-->>Web: 403 Forbidden
                deactivate API

                Web-->>User: "You don't have permission"
                deactivate Web
            end

        else Invalid JWT
            AuthAPI-->>API: Token invalid/expired
            deactivate AuthAPI

            API-->>Web: 401 Unauthorized
            deactivate API

            Web->>AuthAPI: Attempt token refresh
            activate AuthAPI

            alt Refresh Success
                AuthAPI-->>Web: New JWT
                deactivate AuthAPI
                Web->>API: Retry request with new token
                Note over Web,API: Repeat authentication flow

            else Refresh Failed
                AuthAPI-->>Web: Refresh failed
                deactivate AuthAPI
                Web->>Web: Clear session
                Web->>Web: Redirect to /auth/signin
                Web-->>User: "Session expired, please sign in"
                deactivate Web
            end
        end

    else No Session
        AuthUI-->>Web: { isSignedIn: false }
        deactivate AuthUI

        Web->>Web: Redirect to /auth/signin?redirect=/accommodations/create
        Web-->>User: Show signin form
        deactivate Web
    end

    %% Summary
    Note over User,DB: ✅ Key Points:<br/>1. Better Auth manages authentication state<br/>2. JWT tokens authorize API requests<br/>3. Actor context derived from Better Auth user<br/>4. Permissions checked on every request<br/>5. Token refresh handled automatically
